WEBVTT

00:00:05.410 --> 00:00:07.990
Let's talk about the differentiation strategy.

00:00:08.010 --> 00:00:09.230
It is important that you understand very

00:00:09.230 --> 00:00:10.330
well what it consists of and how

00:00:10.330 --> 00:00:11.070
to carry it out.

00:00:12.550 --> 00:00:14.890
As you can see, Porter said there

00:00:14.890 --> 00:00:16.790
are two sources of competitive advantage.

00:00:16.870 --> 00:00:18.610
The first is the low cost and the low cost,

00:00:18.670 --> 00:00:19.390
which we have seen.

00:00:19.890 --> 00:00:21.550
And, on the other hand, to find differentiation.

00:00:21.670 --> 00:00:23.450
And in addition, you can look

00:00:23.450 --> 00:00:24.550
for differentiation in all

00:00:24.550 --> 00:00:25.850
market segments or you can

00:00:25.850 --> 00:00:26.970
sit in a niche, in a particular

00:00:26.970 --> 00:00:27.810
segment.

00:00:28.990 --> 00:00:30.350
It is important to understand

00:00:30.350 --> 00:00:32.290
the criteria for a segmentation

00:00:32.290 --> 00:00:33.390
strategy.

00:00:33.510 --> 00:00:35.430
And the main criterion is that you

00:00:35.430 --> 00:00:36.970
have to identify some factor

00:00:36.970 --> 00:00:39.190
in which you have to be the best.

00:00:39.590 --> 00:00:40.630
You don't have to be the best in everything,

00:00:40.630 --> 00:00:40.970
right?

00:00:40.970 --> 00:00:42.650
You have to identify a factor

00:00:42.650 --> 00:00:44.050
you have to focus on, be very

00:00:44.050 --> 00:00:45.190
good and your customers value

00:00:45.190 --> 00:00:46.050
it, right?

00:00:46.150 --> 00:00:47.910
That's what will allow you to

00:00:47.910 --> 00:00:49.610
successfully implement the

00:00:49.610 --> 00:00:50.890
differentiation strategy.

00:00:51.330 --> 00:00:52.490
Customers need to value it and

00:00:52.490 --> 00:00:53.530
they have to be willing to

00:00:53.530 --> 00:00:54.310
pay for it.

00:00:54.830 --> 00:00:57.070
It is important that you transmit at

00:00:57.070 --> 00:00:59.330
a higher price because you have

00:00:59.330 --> 00:01:01.250
to keep in mind that usually to be

00:01:01.250 --> 00:01:02.570
good at something, to be better than

00:01:02.570 --> 00:01:03.450
others, you'll have to invest

00:01:03.450 --> 00:01:04.870
more than others.

00:01:05.450 --> 00:01:06.610
This usually leads to a

00:01:06.610 --> 00:01:07.690
higher cost structure.

00:01:08.130 --> 00:01:08.910
Therefore, it has to be transmitted

00:01:08.910 --> 00:01:10.910
at a higher price.

00:01:11.830 --> 00:01:13.290
As we said, the differentiation

00:01:13.290 --> 00:01:15.390
strategy can be carried out in

00:01:15.390 --> 00:01:17.870
all segments of the market and

00:01:17.870 --> 00:01:19.770
you will understand it well

00:01:19.770 --> 00:01:20.710
with an example.

00:01:21.030 --> 00:01:23.090
The Mercedes Benz.

00:01:23.430 --> 00:01:25.370
Mercedes Benz has compact cars,

00:01:25.370 --> 00:01:27.830
has all-terrain cars, has family

00:01:28.030 --> 00:01:29.050
members, has sports

00:01:29.050 --> 00:01:30.070
cars, etc.

00:01:30.170 --> 00:01:32.490
We have cars for all segments.

00:01:32.990 --> 00:01:35.010
It is a competition in differentiation.

00:01:35.250 --> 00:01:37.150
Customers choose Mercedes

00:01:37.150 --> 00:01:39.010
not by price, but by

00:01:39.010 --> 00:01:41.770
brand, car characteristics,

00:01:41.770 --> 00:01:42.810
etc.

00:01:44.590 --> 00:01:46.550
However, in the same sector there

00:01:46.550 --> 00:01:49.230
are companies that play in

00:01:49.230 --> 00:01:50.870
differentiation but in small niches.

00:01:51.030 --> 00:01:51.990
A good example would be

00:01:51.990 --> 00:01:52.770
Ferrari.

00:01:53.850 --> 00:01:56.170
Ferrari is only aimed at people with

00:01:56.170 --> 00:01:57.170
a lot of money and also those who

00:01:57.170 --> 00:01:58.570
are lovers of the engine and

00:01:58.570 --> 00:01:59.370
speed, etc.

00:02:00.090 --> 00:02:01.170
What is the key to this

00:02:01.170 --> 00:02:02.790
strategy of focusing on a small

00:02:02.790 --> 00:02:03.970
segment like Ferrari?

00:02:03.970 --> 00:02:05.910
If you want to have a competitive advantage

00:02:05.910 --> 00:02:07.130
in that segment, because it

00:02:07.270 --> 00:02:08.170
is easier for you to know

00:02:08.170 --> 00:02:11.330
that niche very well with which

00:02:11.330 --> 00:02:12.970
you have a very close relationship.

00:02:13.250 --> 00:02:14.990
For Ferrari it is easier

00:02:14.990 --> 00:02:18.550
to meet the needs of its target

00:02:18.550 --> 00:02:20.150
audience, of these people with

00:02:20.150 --> 00:02:21.930
a lot of money than for Mercedes.

00:02:22.050 --> 00:02:23.070
Mercedes is more focused,

00:02:23.070 --> 00:02:24.890
it is in all segments.

00:02:25.870 --> 00:02:27.750
Let's see what are the benefits

00:02:27.750 --> 00:02:31.250
of the differentiation strategy

00:02:31.250 --> 00:02:32.630
over the low cost, because

00:02:32.630 --> 00:02:34.470
it has some benefits.

00:02:34.710 --> 00:02:37.070
I think there is one very important to

00:02:37.070 --> 00:02:39.530
understand and is that when you

00:02:39.530 --> 00:02:41.690
compete in differentiation, in principle

00:02:41.690 --> 00:02:43.510
your competition, the competitive

00:02:43.510 --> 00:02:44.830
struggle will be less.

00:02:45.310 --> 00:02:47.510
And the more differentiated you are,

00:02:47.850 --> 00:02:48.550
the less.

